Pronunciation:
Notes: cf Part: `ineligible - mainly nautical term F. and H.; sup. 3. A blanket :c.: from ca1885 : B and L: ex the nautical S.E. sense. Farmer and Henley Lammy. A blanket: originally a thick quilted frock, or short jumper made of flannel or blanket cloth, worn by sailors as an outside garment in cold weather.  (Gentlemen's Magazine 1866) W3 Lammie, -y; lambie, -y. [Nf OEDS?; EDD [The Ll-spelling might be back-formation from  llama (OED b. The wool of the llama or a material made from this - 1882); c. llama - stuff 1851, llama-cloth 1871 HWO]
